quran[13]{c,v,t,f}:
43,48,"Every Sign that We showed them was greater than its predecessor; and then We seized them with Our chastisement so that they may return (to the Right Way). {1}",footnotes:1:This implies the signs which Allah showed them through the Prophet Moses (peace be upon him) afterwards
43,49,"(Whenever they faced an affliction) they would say: “O magician, pray for us to your Lord according to your station with Him. We shall certainly be guided to the Right Way.”"
43,50,"But lo, each time We removed Our affliction from them, they would go back on their word. {1}",footnotes:1:The stubbornness of Pharaoh and the chiefs of his people can be judged from the fact that when distressed by the torment they wanted the Prophet Moses (peace be upon him) to pray for its removal
43,51,"And Pharaoh proclaimed among his people: {1} “My people, do I not have dominion over Egypt, and are these streams not flowing beneath me? Can't you see? {2}",footnotes:1:Pharaoh probably sent heralds to the cities and towns throughout the country to proclaim what he said in his address to his ministers and courtiers in the capital. Pharaoh could not have availed of the services of a sycophantic press
43,52,"Am I better or this contemptible man {1} who is scarcely able to express himself? {2}",footnotes:1:Who is despicable: the person who has neither wealth
43,53,"Why were bracelets of gold not bestowed upon him? Why did a retinue of angels not accompany him as attendants?” {1}",footnotes:1:In the ancient times when a person was appointed to be governor of a land or sent as an ambassador to a foreign country
43,54,"He incited his people to levity and they obeyed him. Surely they were an iniquitous people. {1}",footnotes:1:A tremendous reality has been expressed in this brief sentence. When a person wishes to become autocratic in a country and contrives every plan openly to achieve his object
43,55,"So when they incurred Our wrath, We exacted retribution from them, and drowned them all,"
43,56,"and made them a thing of the past and an example for those who would come after them. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
43,57,"No sooner the example of the son of Mary was mentioned than, lo and behold, your people raised a clamour"
43,58,"and said: “Who is better, our deities or he?” {1} They said so only out of contentiousness. They are a disputatious people.",footnotes:1:In (verse 45) above
43,59,"He was no more than a servant (of Ours), one upon whom We bestowed Our favours and whom We made an example (of Our infinite power) for the Children of Israel. {1}",footnotes:1:“We made him an example” implies causing the Prophet Jesus (peace be upon him) to be born without a father
43,60,"If We had so willed We could have made some of you into angels {1} to become your successors on earth.",footnotes:1:Another translation can be: make some of you angels.
